\title{Linear Combination}
\taxon{Definition}
\p{
    Let #{V} be a [vector space](def-000H) over a field #{F}.
    Let #{v_1, \dots, v_n} be vectors in #{V}.
    A \strong{linear combination} of #{v_1, \dots, v_n} is an expression of the form
    ##{
        a_1 v_1 + \dots + a_n v_n
    }
    where #{a_1, \dots, a_n \in F}.
}